50|$|The 1366 {{class was}} one of only two pannier tank designs built by the GWR that {{utilised}} <b>outside</b> <b>cylinders,</b> although various existing engines inherited by the GWR had Pannier Tanks and <b>outside</b> <b>cylinders.</b> The 1366 class was developed from the 1361 Class but differed by including a pannier tank rather than a saddle tank, Belpaire firebox, etc. They were designed to replace the 1392 Class.|$|R
